.TH VEK_DOT_I8 3 "2024-01-01" "vek 0.8.0" "Library Functions Manual"
.SH NAME
vek_dot_i8 \- dot product of two int8 vectors
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include <vek.h>
.sp
.BI "int32_t vek_dot_i8(const int8_t *" a ", const int8_t *" b ", size_t " n ");"
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.BR vek_dot_i8 ()
computes the dot product of two signed 8-bit integer vectors:
.PP
.RS
result = sum(a[i] * b[i]) for i = 0 to n-1
.RE
.PP
The result is accumulated in 32 bits to avoid overflow.
.SH PARAMETERS
.TP
.I a
First input vector. Must have at least
.I n
elements.
.TP
.I b
Second input vector. Must have at least
.I n
elements.
.TP
.I n
Number of elements. Must be greater than 0.
.SH RETURN VALUE
Returns the dot product as a 32-bit signed integer.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
int8_t a[] = {1, 2, 3};
int8_t b[] = {4, 5, 6};
int32_t result = vek_dot_i8(a, b, 3);  // 32
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR vek_dot_u8 (3),
.BR vek_dot_f32 (3),
.BR vek_l2sq_i8 (3)
